        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-12-11 23:52:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nI refreshed this to the current master to get this patch moving forward again.\n\nHowever, I see that it is missing the lfsck module in the dkms config file, so it needs to be updated manually.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "42a97a6e5a897a9412fd62341164f0adc75ba2d1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2014-01-22 14:10:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIs this patch relevant anymore? Faccini seems to have a replacement patch for this. If that is the case can this patch be abandoned.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "079a5f2db3a196e1119ebf50ed1d20bfe76ac121",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 192,
        "name": "Brian Behlendorf",
        "email": "behlendorf1@llnl.gov",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-01-22 17:31:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe patches which were just proposed only handle kernel modules on the clients.  Until they address the server case these patches are needed for server builds.\n\nI'm not entirely sure what the objection was to this approach.  It would be nice to know so they could be refreshed accordingly.  These patches are currently applied to the ZoL Lustre repository and until full DKMS support is available in the upstream Lustre tree I'll be maintaining some version of them.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
